We account for the 2- to- 1 stock split on September 1, 2025. We also fine- tune our DPS estimates and our price target. Our valuation remains unchanged.

DHR aims for \(2.0\%\) avg annual growth in stabilized DPS, which is not an easy target for a portfolio built on logistics facilities and rental housing; we will monitor progress. In FT2/25 results, the company explained that it is considering the sale of BTS- type logistics facilities totaling approximately ¥15- 20bn. With the medium- term growth target set for FT8/28, about half of the planned asset sales have already been executed. Attention is now focused on whether the pace of future sales will be adjusted.
Consensus Rating Distribution
Source: Refinitiv, Morgan Stanley Research
DPS same as in our base case.
The dividend yield calculation assumes that the 10y JGB yield (which we use as the risk- free rate) falls 40bps.
Fair value is based on estimated 12- month DPS of ¥6,220 and dividend yield of \(4.0\%\) .
Our base case factors in sales gains on par with the company plan for FT8/25, and FT2/26, but does not allow for gains from FT8/26.
PT is based on our 12- month DPS estimate of ¥6,220 and our target dividend yield of \(4.4\%\) .
DPS undershoots our base case due to a drop in the portfolio occupancy rate as major tenants move out.
The dividend yield calculation assumes that the 10y JGB yield (which we use as the risk- free rate) rises 40bps.
Fair value is based on estimated 12- month DPS of ¥4,980 and dividend yield of \(4.8\%\) .
